    <p>
        <b>1. Srinagar (5,200 ft.)</b></p>
    <p>
     <img src="../TourismHUB/Packages/Images/Kashmir1.jpg" 
            style="height: 226px; width: 884px" />
     </p>
     <p>Srinagar, the summer capital of Jammu & Kashmir (J&K), is split into two by the river Jhelum. The star attraction here is the idyllic Dal Lake, having been ranked TripAdvisor’s top travellers’ choice for 2020. You can take a shikara ride in the daytime or a midnight cruise for a romantic evening. You will also spot Asia’s most extensive Tulip Garden and India’s only floating market here. Hotels in Kashmir cater to all kinds of travellers, so you can book your accommodation accordingly.

Best time to visit: September to November
Ideal Duration: 1-2 days
How to reach:
Nearest Airport: Sheikh ul Alam International Airport (11 km)
Nearest Railway Station: Srinagar Railway Station (12 km)</p>

 
       <p><b>2. Sonmarg (8,960 ft.)</b></p> 
       
   <img src="../TourismHUB/Packages/Images/Kashmir2.jpg" 
            style="height: 226px; width: 884px" />

            <p>Literally meaning the ‘meadow of gold’, Sonmarg observes a widespread bloom of yellow crocuses during spring. Sonmarg or Sonamarg is a high-altitude tourist attraction in Srinagar’s northeast region. It is home to the famous three sisters – a group of rivers (the Lidder, Sind and the Neelum). It is also a popular base point for trekking excursions to the Thajiwas Glacier. While its surreal beauty will leave you stunned, a river rafting experience on the gushing Indus River will get your heart racing.

Sonmarg is truly one of Kashmir’s marvellous attractions that you will want to visit more than once.

Best time to visit: April to June
Ideal duration: 1-2 days
How to reach:
Nearest Airport: Sheikh ul Alam International Airport (102 km)
Nearest Railway Station: Srinagar Railway Station (101 km)</p>

   
    <p><b>3.Aru Valley (7,920 ft.)</b></p> 
    <img src="../TourismHUB/Packages/Images/kashmir3.jpg" 
            style="height: 226px; width: 884px" />
    <p>Aru Valley’s scenic beauty is like a Windows wallpaper image. You can explore the stunning sights of this valley on a pony ride or foot. The drive to this gem of Kashmir is an experience in itself. Book a cosy, local homestay, and savour traditional delicacies at roadside cafes.

The Aru Valley presents unparalleled views of the Kashmir Valley, so if nature and tranquillity are what you seek, you know where to go. You won’t be able to get enough of the natural scenic views here, so don’t miss this gem!

Best time to visit: July to September
Ideal Duration: 2-3 hours
How to reach:
Nearest Airport: Sheikh ul Alam Airport (101 km)
Nearest Railway Station: Srinagar Railway Station (105 km)</p>